## UI-from-image fidelity rules

- Treat the latest supplied screenshot as the source of truth.
- First match the page at the exact reference viewport size before doing responsive adjustments.
- Do not mark the task done if small icons, bullets, carets, stars, button logos, or other micro-details are missing.
- Do not rely on framework defaults for typography when the screenshot differs.
- Do not redesign crowded areas until the exact viewport size, container widths, gaps, and typography have been checked.

